snippet.textDisplay: To everyone thinking that sideloading apps solves the problem, you're over simplifying the problem. People did get google services onto their Mate 30 Pro phones with LZPlay app which accessed administrator settings. The problem was that doing this severely compromised the security of the phone to the point where banking apps no longer worked for anyone that used LZPlay. So unless you want a Mate 30 Pro with no banking apps and compromised security, you can't just "sideload google apps, apk mirror etc etc"
snippet.textOriginal: To everyone thinking that sideloading apps solves the problem, you're over simplifying the problem. People did get google services onto their Mate 30 Pro phones with LZPlay app which accessed administrator settings. The problem was that doing this severely compromised the security of the phone to the point where banking apps no longer worked for anyone that used LZPlay. So unless you want a Mate 30 Pro with no banking apps and compromised security, you can't just "sideload google apps, apk mirror etc etc"
